### Generating Words

The command `hfst-fst2strings` yields a list of all words that can be generated by the mophological parser.
It can also show a given number of entries as seen in the example below.

~~~
$ hfst-fst2strings -n 5 siciliano.generator.hfst
l_aviri+V_FIN+IND+PRES+2+SING:ai
l_aviri+V_FIN+SUBJ+PRES+2+SING:ai
l_aviri+V_FIN+IMP+PRES+2+SING:ai
l_aviri+V_FIN+SUBJ+PRES+1+SING:aia
l_aviri+V_FIN+SUBJ+PRES+3+SING:aia
~~~

### Analyzing Words

The command `hfst-lookup` is used to analyze words:

~~~
$ hfst-lookup it-scn.analyzer.hfst

> non
non l_non+ADV

> dormivo
dormivo l_dormire+V_FIN+IND+IMPERF+1+SING

> durmivu
durmivu l_durmiri+V_FIN+IND+IMPERF+1+SING
durmivu l_durmiri+V_FIN+IND+PAST+1+SING
~~~
